Back room blender/final outputs Pico project.

Default pins:
- GPIO 14: reset button to GND, using internal pull-up
- GPIO 15: blender flour puzzle solved input
- GPIO 16: final output relay/driver input

MQTT publish:
- escape/puzzle/blender/solved
- escape/post/cubby/6/state = ready or completed

MQTT commands:
- escape/game/win
- escape/post/query
- escape/game/reset

When the local reset button is pressed, the Pico republishes its POST state.

Use relay, MOSFET, or isolated driver modules for locks, lights, or powered props.
